{"ticker": "GROQ_INC", "company": "Groq, Inc.", "weight_sum": 1.1400000000000001, "etfs": ["ARKVX", "ARKUX", "ARKSX"], "is_private": true, "query": "\"Groq\" -is:retweet min_faves:10 since_time:1777754140 until_time:1777761643", "n_fetched": 1, "n_kept": 1, "n_dropped": 0, "kept": [{"type": "tweet", "id": "2050622307153109291", "url": "https://x.com/benitoz/status/2050622307153109291", "twitterUrl": "https://twitter.com/benitoz/status/2050622307153109291", "text": "Anthropic in talks with Fractile for SRAM inference chips is the demand-side proof of the thesis I laid out back in January.\n\nThis is the news that proves the SRAM inference thesis isn\u2019t a Groq story it\u2019s an architecture.\n\nFractile, Cerebras, Groq three different vendors, same architectural bet: on-chip SRAM eliminates the HBM shuttle that bottlenecks every autoregressive decode on a GPU. NVIDIA paid ~$20B to bring this capability in-house through the Groq deal. Anthropic is now signaling they want it independent of any single supplier.\n\nThe spending math forces the move. When you\u2019re projecting tens of billions a year on chips, you can\u2019t be one-architecture-deep. SRAM-resident inference isn\u2019t an alternative to HBM-based GPUs it\u2019s the second tier of a disaggregated stack. Prefill and long-context attention stay on HBM. Decode moves to SRAM. The labs that internalize this split fastest get the best tokens-per-megawatt.\n\nI called this the design spectrum: SRAM-only \u2192 SRAM+DDR \u2192 SRAM+HBM. Every frontier model has a different sweet spot on it. Fractile\u2019s value to Anthropic isn\u2019t \u201ccheaper than Nvidia\u201d it\u2019s the architectural freedom to route Claude inference where the physics says it belongs.\n\nWatch the next round of frontier-lab capex announcements. Every one of them is going to have an SRAM line item.\n\nThe Memory Wall (Jan 12): https://t.co/dBgM8UE5xp", "source": "Twitter for iPhone", "retweetCount": 4, "replyCount": 1, "likeCount": 21, "quoteCount": 1, "viewCount": 2038, "createdAt": "Sat May 02 17:03:51 +0000 2026", "lang": "en", "bookmarkCount": 12, "isReply": false, "inReplyToId": null, "conversationId": "2050622307153109291", "displayTextRange": [0, 277], "inReplyToUserId": null, "inReplyToUsername": null, "author": {"type": "user", "userName": "benitoz", "url": "https://x.com/benitoz", "twitterUrl": "https://twitter.com/benitoz", "id": "30399584", "name": "Ben Pouladian", "isVerified": false, "isBlueVerified": true, "verifiedType": null, "profilePicture": "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/1647023468981137408/2Bnlz9S7_normal.jpg", "coverPicture": "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_banners/30399584/1605166024", "description": "", "location": "Los Angeles, CA", "followers": 17800, "following": 1363, "status": "", "canDm": true, "canMediaTag": false, "createdAt": "Sat Apr 11 04:40:54 +0000 2009", "entities": {"description": {"urls": []}, "url": {}}, "fastFollowersCount": 0, "favouritesCount": 62216, "hasCustomTimelines": true, "isTranslator": false, "mediaCount": 4359, "statusesCount": 29563, "withheldInCountries": [], "affiliatesHighlightedLabel": {}, "possiblySensitive": false, "pinnedTweetIds": ["2044039662675866034"], "profile_bio": {"description": "The world isn\u2019t short of oil. It\u2019s short of tokens.\nHardware, software, models. System-level AI infrastructure analysis.\nNVDA since 2016. DMs open \u2193", "entities": {"description": {}, "url": {"urls": [{"display_url": "bepresearch.substack.com", "expanded_url": "https://bepresearch.substack.com/", "indices": [0, 23], "url": "https://t.co/XRTl9r0EcK"}]}}}, "isAutomated": false, "automatedBy": null}, "extendedEntities": {"media": [{"allow_download_status": {"allow_download": true}, "display_url": "pic.twitter.com/iV3VWrfD09", "expanded_url": "https://twitter.com/benitoz/status/2050622307153109291/photo/1", "ext_media_availability": {"status": "Available"}, "features": {"large": {"faces": []}, "orig": {"faces": []}}, "id_str": "2050